DIV1.P:
O the admirable Discord, the melo∣dious Discord, which must carry on the Life of Christianity. A Conversation with a Glorious CHRIST in Heaven;


must carry us up to Heaven. The Life of a Christian is then upon its true Notes, when he is as full of CHRIST and HEAVEN, as is in this Life attainable. Heavenly Contempla∣tions on the Blessed JESUS, Heavenly Consecrations to the Blessed JESUS, Lovely Imitations of Heaven and of JE∣SUS, O Heaven-born Souls, why do you make no greater Improvements in them! And yet I shall do my Can∣didate of the Heavenly Life, no manner of wrong, if I fetch him down from the Suburbs of Heaven, and lay him Groaning and Weeping in the lower parts of the Earth. No, There is a most incomparable Agreement, be∣tween a Conversation with CHRIST, and HEAVEN, and a Conversation that has a continual strain of Repen∣tance abasing of it; They assist each other wonderfully! You shall give me leave, without a Censure of Levity in the expression, to say; The shortest way to Heaven is by Water. The Ex∣pression was of old used in the Church of God. And you are apprised of what it means; It means, the Tears of


a Repenting Soul, which must keep run∣ning from our Eyes, till Death has closed them.
